Under the **Factories Act 1948**, if a worker works more than 9 hours a day or 48 hours a week, they are entitled to overtime wages at twice the ordinary wage rate. For IT/ITES employees under the Shops and Establishments Act, overtime rules vary by state. This calculator computes overtime wages based on your basic daily/hourly rate and extra hours worked.
